{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a28fbb98-c473-4f8e-bab9-26511ead54e7","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed **above** them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_VlfttpnczoXATyQERlUbkY","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3efe54b858594b48aa0a6cd8e8f97946/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-3efe54b858594b48aa0a6cd8e8f97946/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"d4f7d296-42a4-484f-8e24-0514836e6f5b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed **before** them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"1926:3F91FF:13FF842:165828E:6A066E88"},"id":"a263b191-1b90-40bb-96b2-d2d439cb65cb","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:40.063Z","parentId":"7b631f6d-52b4-4bdc-b3cf-db6fb4a9895a"}
